sepals is an independent Python implementation of the separated
regression method described by:

Gregory Beylkin, Jochen Garcke, and Martin J. Mohlenkamp,
"Multivariate Regression and Machine Learning with Sums of Separable Functions",
submitted December 2007; revised September 2008.
PDF: https://ins.uni-bonn.de/media/public/publication-media/BE-GA-MO2007P.pdf?pk=625

Algorithmic credit:
- Separated representation as sums of products of one-dimensional factors.
- Alternating least-squares reduction to one-dimensional subproblems.
- Linear normal-equation formulation for basis-expanded one-dimensional factors.
- Smoothness regularization by adding basis-dependent diagonal penalties.
- Multilevel tent basis construction.

This repository contains an independent implementation. The license in this
repository applies only to this implementation code and documentation. It does
not relicense the paper, paper text, paper figures, third-party datasets, or
benchmark results.
